eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu has the details .#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Twenty-seven people accused of being part of a fake passport syndicate will remain behind bars, for now. The suspects appeared at the Krugersdorp Magistrate’s Court on Monday. They were arrested in a sting operation at the Krugersdorp Home Affairs office on Friday. A Pakistani national, believed to be the kingpin, was also arrested.
  
It is believed the syndicate involves corrupt Home Affairs officials. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu has the details in the video above. 